of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  French: habitational name from any of the places so called, for example in Normandy, named from a religious dedication to a (male) St. Clair.","2  North American variant spelling of   St  .   Claire  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Claire","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Clare  .","Variant of   Clair  , an altered form of German   Klare  .","French: variant of   Clair  ."]}]},{"name":"Clair","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: from the male personal name <i>Clair</i> (from Latin <i>Clarus</i> ‘illustrious’), which was borne by two early Christian saints, a 3rd-century bishop of Nantes and the 4th-century St. Clair of Aquitaine.","French: nickname for a cheerful individual, from the adjective <i>clair</i> ‘bright, light’. Compare   Leclair   1.","American shortened form of French   Leclair   1, a cognate of 2 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Leclair","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre, Armand, Emile, Normand, Gaston, Adrien, Antoine, Lucien, Monique, Philias, Camille.","French: nickname for a cheerful individual, a variant of   Clair   2 ‘bright, light’, with fused masculine definite article <i>le</i>. Derivation from the male personal name   Clair   1 is also possible. Compare   Laclair  ,   Laclaire  , and   Leclear  .","French: altered form of   Leclerc   1."]},{"name":"Klar","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Ezriel, Tzvi, Baruch, Devorah, Isadore, Nachman, Yitzchok.  German Gerhard, Johann, Erhard, Kurt, Willibald.","German: nickname from Middle High German and Middle Low German <i>klār</i> ‘pure, beautiful, clear’.","German: from the female personal name <i>Klara</i>, an equivalent of <i>Clara</i> (see   Clair   and   Sinclair  )."]},{"name":"Cler","meanings":["French: variant of   Clair  ."]},{"name":"Clarin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Luz, Alejandro, Armida, Epifano, Florencio, Jose, Libia, Librada, Maria Luisa, Raul, Santos, Sergio.","Swedish: variant of <b>Klarin</b>, ornamental or perhaps habitational name formed with <i>klar</i> ‘clear’ (possibly representing an element of a placename) + the adjectival suffix <i>-in</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>-in(i)us</i> ‘relating to’.","French: from a pet form of the personal name   Clair  ."]},{"name":"Auclair","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Marcel, Raoul, Andre, Fernand, Ovila, Alphonse, Cecile, Gaston, Germaine, Jacques, Jean-Paul.","French: patronymic from   Clair  , from <i>(fils) au Clair</i> ‘(son) of Clair’. Compare   Leclerc   2 and   Oclair  .","History: Pierre and André Auclair, two brothers from Saint-Vivien near La Rochelle in France, are recorded in Charlesbourg, QC, in 1679 and 1681, respectively, the years of their marriage. The descendants of one or another brother also bear altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Leclerc</i>, <i>Oclair</i>, and <i>O'Clair</i>."]}]},{"name":"Amaury","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Cecile, Chantal, Christophe, Jean-Luc, Lucien, Marcel, Michel, Monique, Phillippe, Sylvanie.  Spanish Jose, Ruben, Carlos, Manuel, Alvaro, Antolin, Luis, Miguel, Pedro, Ramon, Roberto, Salvador.","French (mainly southern): from a regional variant of the personal name   Maurin  .","French: from a shortened form of the personal name <i>Amaury</i> (see   Amery  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Maurin","meanings":["Pet form of   Máire ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Chaumont","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Gilles, Raoul, Yvon.  Spanish Alicia, Andres, Arturo, Beatriz, Elia, Jose, Julio, Miguel, Raul.","French: habitational name from any of numerous places called Chaumont ‘bald mountain’ (ultimately from Latin <i>calvus mons</i>), for example in Cher, Orne, Jura, Haute-Savoie.","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Chaumont in Orne (see 1 above)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Lord","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Lorraine   or variant spelling of   Laurie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lorraine","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, in origin denoting a migrant from the province of <i>Lorraine</i> in eastern France. This derives its name from Latin <i>Lotharingia</i> ‘territory of the people of <i>Lothar</i>’. The latter is a Germanic personal name derived from <i>hlud</i> ‘fame’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. <i>Lorraine</i> began to be used as a girl's name in Scotland in the 19th century, and for a time in the second half of the 20th century enjoyed great popularity, which has since waned."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Amaury Robert de Chaumont Lord St Clair was born about 1160, in Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France, his father, Robert de Chaumont II - Sixth Seigneur De Chaumont, was 27 and his mother, Lady Richilde Sinclair - Lady of Roslin, was 26. He married Isabella de Rosslin before 1190, in France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1248, in Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland, at the age of 90, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"about 1160–about 1248":"umbes 1160–umbes 1248","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"umbes 1248","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"enne 1190","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1160–about 1248":"noin 1160–noin 1248","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"noin 1160","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"noin 1248","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"ennen vuotta 1190","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, Ranska","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Ranska","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1160–about 1248":"environ 1160–environ 1248","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"environ 1160","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"environ 1248","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"avant 1190","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Écosse","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, France","Scotland":"Écosse","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Amaury Robert de Chaumont Lord St Clair est né environ 1160, à Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France, son père, Robert de Chaumont II - Sixth Seigneur De Chaumont, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Lady Richilde Sinclair - Lady of Roslin, avait 26 ans. Il a épousé Isabella de Rosslin avant 1190, à France. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé environ 1248, à Roslin, Midlothian, Écosse, à l’âge de 90 ans, et a été enterré à Écosse."},"de":{"about 1160–about 1248":"um 1160–um 1248","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"um 1160","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"um 1248","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"vor 1190","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, Frankreich","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Frankreich","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Als Amaury Robert de Chaumont Lord St Clair um 1160 in Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Frankreich geboren wurde, war sein Vater Robert de Chaumont II - Sixth Seigneur De Chaumont 27 und seine Mutter Lady Richilde Sinclair - Lady of Roslin 26. Er hat vor 1190 in Frankreich Isabella de Rosslin geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb um 1248 im Alter von 90 Jahren in Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland und wurde in Scotland begraben."},"ht":{"about 1160–about 1248":"about 1160–about 1248","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"about 1160","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"about 1248","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"before 1190","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, France","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France","France":"France"},"hu":{"about 1160–about 1248":"1160 körül–1248 körül","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"1160 körül","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"1248 körül","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"1190 előtt","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, Franciaország","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Franciaország","France":"Franciaország"},"id":{"about 1160–about 1248":"sekitar 1160–sekitar 1248","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"sekitar 1160","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"sekitar 1248","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"sebelum 1190","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, Prancis","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Prancis","France":"Prancis"},"it":{"about 1160–about 1248":"circa 1160–circa 1248","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1134–1174":"1134–1174","1135–1165":"1135–1165","1190":"1190","about 1160":"circa 1160","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"circa 1248","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"prima del 1190","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, Francia","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Francia","France":"Francia","lifeSummary":"Quando Amaury Robert de Chaumont Lord St Clair è nato il circa 1160 nel Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Francia, il suo padre, Robert de Chaumont II - Sixth Seigneur De Chaumont, aveva 27 anni e il suo madre, Lady Richilde Sinclair - Lady of Roslin, aveva 26 anni. Lui sposato Isabella de Rosslin prima del 1190, nel Francia. Erano genitori di almeno 1 figlio. Morì circa 1248, nel Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland, all'età di 90 anni, e fu sepolto a Scotland."},"ja":{"about 1160–about 1248":"約1160年–約1248年","1155–1185":"1155年–1185年","1155–1224":"1155年–1224年","1160–1248":"1160年–1248年","1165–1252":"1165年–1252年","1190–1248":"1190年–1248年","1134–1174":"1134年–1174年","1135–1165":"1135年–1165年","1190":"1190年","about 1160":"約1160年","1165":"1165年","1252":"1252年","1174":"1174年","1185":"1185年","1160":"1160年","1248":"1248年","1224":"1224年","1135":"1135年","about 1248":"約1248年","1134":"1134年","1155":"1155年","before 1190":"1190年以前","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"スコットランドミドロスアンロスリン","Oise, Picardie, France":"フランスピカーディオイゼ","Scotland":"スコットランド","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"フランスピカーディオイゼチャウモント","France":"フランス","lifeSummary":"Amaury Robert de Chaumont Lord St Clairが約1160年にフランスピカーディオイゼチャウモントで生まれた時，父Robert de Chaumont II - Sixth Seigneur De Chaumontは27歳，母Lady Richilde Sinclair - Lady of Roslinは26歳であった。1190年以前にフランスでIsabella de Rosslinと結婚した。彼らは少なくとも1人の息子の親であった。彼は約1248年にスコットランドミドロスアンロスリンで90歳で死去し，スコットランドにて埋葬された。"},"ko":{"about 1160–about 1248":"대략 1160년–대략 1248년","1155–1185":"1155년–1185년","1155–1224":"1155년–1224년","1160–1248":"1160년–1248년","1165–1252":"1165년–1252년","1190–1248":"1190년–1248년","1134–1174":"1134년–1174년","1135–1165":"1135년–1165년","1190":"1190년","about 1160":"대략 1160년","1165":"1165년","1252":"1252년","1174":"1174년","1185":"1185년","1160":"1160년","1248":"1248년","1224":"1224년","1135":"1135년","about 1248":"대략 1248년","1134":"1134년","1155":"1155년","before 1190":"1190년 이전","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"스컷랜드 미들로스이언 로슬린","Oise, Picardie, France":"프랑스 피카디 이스","Scotland":"스컷랜드","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"프랑스 피카디 이스 차몽","France":"프랑스","lifeSummary":"Amaury Robert de Chaumont Lord St Clair(이)가 대략 1160년 프랑스 피카디 이스 차몽에서 태어났을 때, 그의 아버지 Robert de Chaumont II - Sixth Seigneur De Chaumont(은)는 27세였고, 그의 어머니 Lady Richilde Sinclair - Lady of Roslin(은)는 26세였다. 그는 1190년 이전 프랑스에서 Isabella de Rosslin(와)과 결혼했다. 그들은 적어도 한 명의 아들을 두었다. 그는 대략 1248년 스컷랜드 미들로스이언 로슬린에서 90세의 나이로 사망했으며 스컷랜드에 묻혔다."},"lv":{"about 1160–about 1248":"ap 1160. gadu–ap 1248. gadu","1155–1185":"1155–1185","1155–1224":"1155–1224","1160–1248":"1160–1248.gads","1165–1252":"1165.gads–1252","1190–1248":"1190.gads–1248.gads","1134–1174":"1134–1174.gads","1135–1165":"1135–1165.gads","1190":"1190. gads","about 1160":"ap 1160. gadu","1165":"1165. gads","1252":"1252","1174":"1174. gads","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1248":"1248. gads","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1248":"ap 1248. gadu","1134":"1134","1155":"1155","before 1190":"pirms 1190. gada","Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland":"Roslin, Midlothian, Scotland","Oise, Picardie, France":"Oise, Picardie, Francija","Scotland":"Scotland","Chaumont, Oise,